results.occurrenceRemarks: These forest buffalo were just 100 meters away from where we were walking in the middle of the night!  We were on the beach and they were in the floodplain, but still!  Gave me a few chills to see the signs the next morning.  I typically don't pay a lot of attention to subspecies designations but the smaller size and conspicuous color of African buffalo in Central African forests compel me to denote S. c. nanus here.
